cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.SE. 

The paper discusses a methodology for deriving uniform characterizations of different declarative semantics for logic programs with negation, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic (cs.LO). The paper also mentions the well-founded semantics and the Fitting (or Kripke-Kleene) semantics, which are topics in programming languages (cs.PL) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper aims to provide a coherent picture of relations between different semantics for normal logic programs, which is a topic in software engineering (cs.SE).
